<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="42.[151,1437,690,895]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
A western Palearctic genus of small-sized skinks with 10 currently recognized species, two of which occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[1384,1433,763,786]" name="Iran" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Iran</collectingCountry>
. The genus appears sister to the central and east-Asian 
<taxonomicName box="[780,952,798,823]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Asymblepharus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[780,952,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Asymblepharus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although only one representative of each genus was analyzed (
<bibRefCitation author="Pyron, R. &amp; Burbrink, F. &amp; Wiens, J." box="[391,594,834,859]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="93" refId="ref62209" refString="Pyron, R., Burbrink, F. &amp; Wiens, J. (2013) A phylogeny and revised classification of Squamata, including 4161 species of lizards and snakes. BMC Evolutionary Biology, 13, 93. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1186 / 1471 - 2148 - 13 - 93" type="journal article" year="2013">
Pyron 
<emphasis box="[468,525,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). For the time being there is no phylogenetic study where both the Iranian species would be included at once.
</paragraph>
